The paper deals with network-based methods for analyzing political interaction on social media, which involves social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of web domains and links, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper focuses on the analysis of large-scale data, which is a common theme in the sub-category of social informatics (cs.SI).
